President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Dr. Greg Autry to the position of Chief Financial Officer at the National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA). Dr. Autry is currently an Assistant Professor of Clinical Entrepreneurship at the University of Southern California, where he researches and teaches technology commercialization. He also teaches graduate courses in space entrepreneurship at the International Space University Center for Space Entrepreneurship. Additionally, Dr. Autry directs the Pacific Commercial Spaceflight Initiative at the Aldrin Space Institute. He serves as the Chair of the Safety Working Group on the Commercial Space Transportation Advisory Committee with the FAA's Office of Commercial Space Transportation and is the Vice President for Space Development at the National Space Society. Dr. Autry has previously served on the NASA Agency Review Team and as the White House Liaison at NASA. He holds an MBA and a PhD from the University of California, Irvine, as well as a B.A. from the California Polytechnic University, Pomona.